35 (b) It shall be unlawful for any person, organization, corporation, hospital, facilitator, or
36 association of any kind whatsoever to sell, offer to sell, or conspire with another to sell or
37 offer to sell a child for money or anything of value, except as otherwise provided in this
38 article.
39 (c)(1) As used in this subsection, the term 'inducements' means any financial assistance,
40 either direct or indirect, from whatever source, but shall expressly not include:
41 (A) The payment or reimbursement of the medical expenses directly related to the
42 biological mother's pregnancy and hospitalization for the birth of the child and medical
43 care for such child if paid by a licensed child-placing agency or an attorney;
